'''GOG.com'''（旧称Good Old Game）是一家提供[[电子游戏|电子游戏]]和[[电影|电影]]的[[数字发行|数字发行]]平台，它由GOG公司运营，母公司為[[CD_Projekt|CD Projekt]]。GOG公司的總部位于波兰[[华沙|华沙]]。<ref>{{cite web|title=Shape your career with GOG.com|url=http://www.gog.com/work#gog_mentality|work=GOG.com|accessdate=20 January 2014|archive-date=2019-06-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190622193840/https://www.gog.com/work#gog_mentality|dead-url=no}}</ref>GOG.com通过无[[数字版权管理|数字版权管理]]（DRM-free）的方式提供适用于[[Windows|Windows]]、[[OS_X|OS X]]和[[Linux|Linux]]平台的电子游戏。在早期，GOG只發行年代較久的遊戲，自2012年3月，它开始售卖较为新款的游戏。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.vg247.com/2012/03/24/gog-com-to-become-bigger-fresher-newer-on-march-27/ |title=GoG.com to become "bigger, fresher, newer" on March 27 |first=Stephany |last=Nunneley |date=2012-03-24 |work=VG24/7 |accessdate=2014-11-09 |archive-date=2016-03-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160303205229/http://www.vg247.com/2012/03/24/gog-com-to-become-bigger-fresher-newer-on-march-27/ |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.techspot.com/news/50549-good-old-games-brings-all-time-classics-to-the-mac.html |title=Good Old Games brings all-time classics to the Mac |first=Jose |last=Vilches |date=2012-10-19 |work=[[TechSpot|TechSpot]] |accessdate=2012-12-05 |archive-date=2016-08-17 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160817085710/http://www.techspot.com/news/50549-good-old-games-brings-all-time-classics-to-the-mac.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>

1994年Marcin Iwiński和Michał Kiciński创建了CD Projekt公司。他们最初从美国批发商原装进口游戏并在波兰出售。<ref name="eurog_cdprojekt_history">{{cite web | url=http://www.eurogamer.net/articles/2013-11-06-seeing-red-the-story-of-cd-projekt | title=Seeing Red: The story of CD Projekt | work=[[Eurogamer|Eurogamer]] | publisher=Gamer Network | first=Robert | last=Purchese | date=2015-05-17 | accessdate=2015-08-25 | archive-date=2013-11-07 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131107171150/http://www.eurogamer.net/articles/2013-11-06-seeing-red-the-story-of-cd-projekt | dead-url=no }}</ref>2008年后期，CD Projekt推出了GOG.com。最初的目的是发行没有数字版权管理的经典游戏。<ref name="gspot_gog_six">{{cite web | url=http://www.gamespot.com/articles/gog-celebrates-six-years-of-advancing-the-drm-free/1100-6422150/ | title=GOG Celebrates Six Years of Advancing the "DRM-Free Movement" | work=[[GameSpot|GameSpot]] | publisher=[[CBS_Interactive|CBS Interactive]] | first=Eddie | last=Makuch | date=2014-09-08 | accessdate=2015-08-25 | archive-date=2015-09-04 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150904113659/http://www.gamespot.com/articles/gog-celebrates-six-years-of-advancing-the-drm-free/1100-6422150/ | dead-url=no }}</ref>

== 历史 ==
[[File:GOG.com_old_logo.png|thumb]]

2017年6月22日，GOG.com加入了简体中文支持以及[[人民币|人民币]]结算。在结算方面，支持[[支付宝|支付宝]]、[[银联|银联]]、[[微信|微信]]、[[财付通|财付通]]等支付方式<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.gamersky.com/news/201706/918899.shtml|title=GOG平台开通国区 支持支付宝微信等付款方式|accessdate=2017-06-23|author=梁萧|date=2017-06-22|publisher=[[游民星空|游民星空]]|language=zh-cn|archive-date=2018-03-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180304172604/http://www.gamersky.com/news/201706/918899.shtml|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

==特色==
GOG.com發行的{{link-en|數位商品|digital goods}}（電子遊戲或電影）可以[[數位發行|從網路上購買和下載]]，而且這些商品沒有[[數位版權管理|數位版權管理]]（DRM）的限制，<ref name="arsinterview">{{cite web |url=http://arstechnica.com/gaming/news/2008/09/idiocy-of-games-drm.ars |title=Good Old Games and the 'idiocy' of DRM |accessdate=2008-09-27 |first=Frank |last=Caron |date=2008-09-25 |publisher=[[Ars_Technica|Ars Technica]] |archive-date=2011-01-21 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110121192543/http://arstechnica.com/gaming/news/2008/09/idiocy-of-games-drm.ars |dead-url=no }}</ref>，也就是說這些產品沒有下載/安裝次數的限制，使用者可以把檔案複製/安裝到任意數量的電腦或其他裝置上，並且不需要安裝額外的用戶端軟體（例如[[Steam|Steam]]或[[Origin_(電子遊戲平台)|Origin]]）就能使用這些產品。老遊戲的價格通常在5或10美元之間，不時也有特價活動。部份較新的遊戲價格較高。GOG.com的數位產品也可以以禮物兌換碼的方式贈送給他人。<ref>[http://www.gog.com/support/website_help/gift_certificates Website Help Gift certificates] {{Wayback|url=http://www.gog.com/support/website_help/gift_certificates |date=20160602100131 }} on GOG.com</ref>

GOG.com发行的游戏都是用[[Inno_Setup|Inno Setup]]打包成的，且对安装包进行了加密。后经玩家反对<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.gog.com/wishlist/site/dont_slip_into_drm_swamp_stop_using_password_protection_on_installer_packages|title=Don't slip into DRM swamp - stop using password protection on installer packages!|accessdate=2018-03-04|author=|date=|publisher=GOG.com|language=en|archive-date=2018-11-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181112142927/https://www.gog.com/wishlist/site/dont_slip_into_drm_swamp_stop_using_password_protection_on_installer_packages|dead-url=no}}</ref>，之后发行的游戏中取消了对安装包的加密。但部分早前发行的游戏（如[[刺客教條_(遊戲)|刺客信条]]）的安装包仍被加密。

使用者並不需要安裝特別的[[用戶端|用戶端]]軟體就能下載或執行遊戲，<ref name="arspreview">{{cite web |url=http://arstechnica.com/gaming/news/2008/09/first-look-gog-revives-classic-pc-games-for-download-age.ars |title=First look: GOG revives classic PC games for download age |accessdate=2008-09-27 |first=Frank |last=Caron |date=2008-09-09 |publisher=[[Ars_Technica|Ars Technica]] |archive-date=2012-04-02 |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/66dMJ1ruP?url=http://arstechnica.com/gaming/news/2008/09/first-look-gog-revives-classic-pc-games-for-download-age.ars |dead-url=no }}</ref>不過使用者仍然可以使用下載管理（將被淘汰）<ref name="goggalaxyfaq">{{cite web |url=http://www.gog.com/galaxy#glx-faq |accessdate=2015-05-14 |title=GOG Galaxy FAQ |archive-date=2021-02-02 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210202160629/https://www.gog.com/galaxy#glx-faq |dead-url=no }}</ref>或GOG Galaxy用戶端軟體來下載產品。下載之後，使用者可以把軟體用在任何個人用途上，例如安裝到多個裝置，<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.gog.com/support/website_help/downloads_and_games |title=GOG.com FAQ |date=2014-12-27 |accessdate=2014-12-27 |publisher=GOG.com |quote=''Can I enjoy my purchases both on my laptop and desktop computer at home? Yes. We do not limit the number of installations or reinstallations, as long as you install your purchased games on computers in your household.'' |archive-date=2012-11-20 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121120100304/http://www.gog.com/support/website_help/downloads_and_games |dead-url=no }}</ref>不限次數的保存到任何個人的[[儲存裝置|儲存裝置]]上，製作[[遊戲模組|遊戲模組]]或修改遊戲檔案；限制是使用者不可再次販售或分享產品。<ref name="academia.edu"/>軟體的安裝檔案技術上來說是不依賴GOG.com上的帳號就能使用的，不過根據GOG.com的[[EULA|EULA]]，產品是「授權使用的，而非販售」的。<ref name="academia.edu">{{Cite web |url=http://www.academia.edu/6129809/GOG.com_End-User_License_Agreement |title=Academia.edu |accessdate=2016-04-24 |archive-date=2020-01-08 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200108203155/https://www.academia.edu/6129809/GOG.com_End-User_License_Agreement |dead-url=no }}</ref>這種商業模式時常引起數位商品的所有權的疑問。<ref name="doweownsteamgames">{{cite web |url=http://www.rockpapershotgun.com/2012/02/01/thought-do-we-own-our-steam-games/ |title=Thought: Do We Own Our Steam Games? |publisher=[[Rock,_Paper,_Shotgun|Rock, Paper, Shotgun]] |first=John |last=Walker |date=2012-02-01 |accessdate=2014-12-27 |quote=''I asked gamer lawyer Jas Purewal about this a short while back, not specifically about Valve, and he explained that the matter is still unresolved. "In fact," he says, "it's never been completely resolved for software generally[...]"'' |archive-date=2013-06-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130604011532/http://www.rockpapershotgun.com/2012/02/01/thought-do-we-own-our-steam-games/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>在[[歐盟|歐盟]]，[[歐盟法庭|歐盟法庭]]主張版權持有者不能反對他人再次販售已經購買的軟體，依據針對首次販售的版權窮竭法令，產品所有權在販售時已經轉移，因此這種「授權而非販售」的EULA受到了質疑。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.gamerlaw.co.uk/2012/the-legality-of-second-hand-software-sales-in-the-eu/ |title=The legality of second hand software sales in the EU |first=Jas |last=Purewal |publisher=gamerlaw.co.uk |accessdate=2016-04-24 |archive-date=2020-01-08 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200108203926/http://www.gamerlaw.co.uk/2012/the-legality-of-second-hand-software-sales-in-the-eu/ |dead-url=no }} ([http://www.gamasutra.com/view/news/173538/ mirror] {{Wayback|url=http://www.gamasutra.com/view/news/173538/ |date=20200807031411 }} on [[gamasutra.com|gamasutra.com]])</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.dw.de/dw/article/0,,16069323,00.html |title=Oracle loses court fight over software resale rules |quote=''A European court has ruled that it's permissible to resell software licenses even if the package has been downloaded directly from the Internet. It sided with a German firm in its legal battle with US giant Oracle.'' |date=2012-07-03 |accessdate=2014-12-30 |author=hg/mz (AFP, dpa) |publisher=[[dw.de|dw.de]] |archive-date=2012-09-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120903163715/http://www.dw.de/dw/article/0,,16069323,00.html |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="ecjforbes">{{cite web |url=http://www.forbes.com/sites/gregvoakes/2012/07/03/european-courts-rule-in-favor-of-consumers-reselling-downloaded-games/ |publisher=[[forbes.com|forbes.com]] |first=Greg |last=Voakes |title=European Courts Rule In Favor Of Consumers Reselling Downloaded Games |date=2012-07-03 |accessdate=2014-12-30 |quote=''Could this be the victory we need for a "gamer's bill of rights" ? DRM is an oft-cited acronym, and resonates negatively in the gaming community. The Court of Justice of the European Union ruled in favor of reselling downloaded games. Simply put, legally purchased and downloaded games will be treated like physical copies of the game, and consumers can then sell their 'used' game.'' |archive-date=2020-11-12 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201112011037/https://www.forbes.com/sites/gregvoakes/2012/07/03/european-courts-rule-in-favor-of-consumers-reselling-downloaded-games/ |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://curia.europa.eu/juris/document/document.jsf?docid=124564&doclang=en |title=JUDGMENT OF THE COURT (Grand Chamber) |date=2012-07-03 |quote=''(Legal protection of computer programs — Marketing of used licences for computer programs downloaded from the internet — Directive 2009/24/EC — Articles 4(2) and 5(1) — Exhaustion of the distribution right — Concept of lawful acquirer)'' |publisher=InfoCuria – Case-law of the Court of Justice |accessdate=2014-12-30 |archive-date=2014-12-31 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141231000941/http://curia.europa.eu/juris/document/document.jsf?docid=124564&doclang=en |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://arstechnica.com/tech-policy/2012/07/top-eu-court-upholds-right-to-resell-downloaded-software/ |title=Top EU court upholds right to resell downloaded software |author=Timothy B. Lee |date=2012-07-03 |publisher=[[Ars_Technica|Ars Technica]] |accessdate=2016-04-24 |archive-date=2014-12-31 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141231010612/http://arstechnica.com/tech-policy/2012/07/top-eu-court-upholds-right-to-resell-downloaded-software/ |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://abcnews.go.com/Technology/wireStory/eu-court-oks-resale-software-licenses-16704351 |title=EU Court OKs Resale of Software Licenses |publisher=AP |accessdate=2016-04-24 |archive-date=2012-07-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120704031817/http://abcnews.go.com/Technology/wireStory/eu-court-oks-resale-software-licenses-16704351 |dead-url=no }}</ref>

